description.plain: The Backyardigans is a CGI-animated musical TV series created by Janice Burgess. It is a co-production of animation studio Nelvana and Nickelodeon Animation Studios. The series debuted on October 11, 2004 and ended on May 31, 2010. The show airs on Treehouse TV in Canada. In 2015, the first season was included as part of Nick Jr.’s Noggin app, a mobile application featuring episodes of older Nick Jr.

description.plain:
“Castaways” is a song featured in Season 1, Episode 11 of the computer-animated children’s show The Backyardigans. The song features three of the main characters—Uniqua, Pablo, and Tyrone—who are pretending to be castaways on a desert island.

The song began trending on TikTok in May of 2021.

39 ContributorsTranslationsDeutschCastaways Lyrics[Part I]

[Chorus: All]
Castaways, we are castaways
Ahoy there, ahoy, we are castaways
We're stuck where we are with no house, no car
Castaways, ahoy, we are castaways

[Verse: Uniqua & Pablo]
We were out at sea on a sailing ship
The rain began to rain and the wind began to whip
We felt the ship tip, it was going down
So we launched our lifeboat so we wouldn't drown
[Chorus: All]
Castaways, we are castaways

[Verse: Uniqua, Pablo & Tyrone]
In our little rubber boat, we floated all night
'Til we landed on a shore in the morning light
On a lovely little island where it's just us three
And the sun and the sand and the sky and the sea

[Chorus: All]
Now we're castaways, we are castaways
Ahoy there, ahoy, we are castaways
Not a cup or a dish, eating seaweed and fish
Castaways, ahoy, we are castaways
Castaways, we are castaways
Ahoy there, ahoy, we are castaways on an island at sea

songs.title: Into the Thick of It!

description.plain:
“Into The Thick Of It!” is an opera style song featured in The Backyardigans episode “The Heart of the Jungle.” Uniqua, Pablo, Tyrone, and Austin sing as they travel with no guide to find the heart of the jungle and soon realize they have been walking in circles.

Just like Castaways, this also started trending on TikTok in May, 2021.
